main event: An unidentified object was observed in the sky near Cabot, Arkansas on May 22, 1967.
interesting points: The object was seen at an elevation of 20° and later 13°,It appeared as a large star that sometimes had a spoon shape,The object had lights on the top and one on the bottom,The observer claimed to have seen the object for about forty minutes,The preparing officer opined that the object might be a planet or satellite in orbit.
witness description: Observer was male, 45 years old, from Cabot, Arkansas, occupation and education unknown.
